                                 MAX and MIN


Common macro names for maximum and minimum of two variables.

GNU libc's and FreeBSD's sys/param.h have most common definitions:

  #define MIN(a,b) (((a)<(b))?(a):(b))
  #define MAX(a,b) (((a)>(b))?(a):(b))

For type safety, see REFERENCES.


                                  REFERENCES


- http://stackoverflow.com/q/3437404/242583
